Tools to make a DMG with program.app and all libs ready to be installed in MacOS Applications

Compile and place in path dylibbundler in macdylibbundler.

Compile your program (which you want to make a app from).

Create a folder program. See sz81 folder as example.

Inside this folder create a folder program.app.

Inside program.app create a folder Contents. Inside place your info.plist file.

Inside Contents create a folder MacOS. Inside place your program und the run script.

Inside Contents create a second folder Resources. Inside place the generated icon icns file.

Run makeapplibs scripts with program name. Script must be inside same folder.
dylibbundler now idestifies required libs for your program, creates a libs folder inside Contents and alters yout program to use this copied libs.

Create a icon.png file and place it inside png-to-icns folder. Start png-to-icns.sh. Copy created icns file into Ressources folder.

Any addtional files needed by your program must be placed in MacOS folder.
